name: ukiyo-e #7
description:
Fine Woodblock print - pencil redrawing.

High quality printable artworks now strongly sought after by art enthusiasts all over the world.

Japanese woodblock printing originated in ancient China and was brought to Japan after the unification of the country and Shogunat rule was established. 
Japanese woodblock prints, also called ukiyo-e (which means image of the floating world), are a traditional art form, which started to grow very popular in the newly created capital Edo (now Tokyo) from around 1600.

High quality 4000 x 5500px artwork.
